n error-prone external parsers nor requires modifying the datastore at scale—structural signatures are computed on-the-fly and stored efficiently using product quantization. Moreover, because the probes are trained specifically to align with the model’s own representational geometry, they capture 'model-aware' structure rather than idealized grammar, leading to more effective retrieval. This approach significantly improves robustness in low-resource domains and rare syntactic phenomena, where shallow similarity fails due to sparsity. It also enhances interpretability: by inspecting which probe dimensions activate during retrieval, we can diagnose whether the system prioritized voice, coordination, or entity typing in selecting neighbors.",
